section.para:
A validating resolver is a DNS recursive name server that performs validation for each remote response received, following the chain of trust to verify the answers it receives are legitimate through the magic of crypto and hashing functions. To enable DNSSEC validation on a BIND 9 recursive name server is easy, you only need these three lines of configuration in your configuration file:
      dnssec-enable yes;
dnssec-validation auto;
dnssec-lookaside auto;
